          <h1> Getting Started with HTML Notes </h1>
               <p> 
                    Notes from, and project for, "Stage 0: Getting Started with HTML" within 
                    Udacity's 
                    <a href="https://www.udacity.com/course/intro-to-programming-nanodegree--nd000">
                    Intro to Programming Nanodegree </a>
               </p>


          <br>
          <h2> World Wide Web Composition </h2>
               The web is largely composed of HTML documents: 
               <ul>
                    <li> HTML = <u>H</u>yper<u>T</u>ext 
                                        <u>M</u>arkup 
                                        <u>L</u>anguage 
                    <li> Hypertext = text which contains links to other texts
                    <li> HTML = the language web browsers use to interpret web pages
               </ul>

               The components of the web include:
               <ul>
                    <li> The Client = your computer and browser
                    <li> The Internet = the world's largest computer network
                    <li> Servers = computers that host the files that make up the web
               </ul>

               The client and servers interact through HTTP:
               <ul>
                    <li> HTTP = <u>H</u>yper<u>T</u>ext 
                                       <u>T</u>ransfer 
                                       <u>P</u>rotocol
                    <li> Protocol = a standard that specifies how data are 
                                          transmitted between computers
               </ul>


          <br>
          <h2> HTML Components </h2>
               HTML is made up of:
               <ul>
                    <li> Text content = what you see
                    <li> Markup = what it looks like
                    <li> References to other documents (e.g., images and videos)
               </ul>
          
               HTML Markup is made up of: 
               <ul> 
                    <li> Elements = components that tell the web browser how to display 
                                            content on a web page
                    <li> Tags = keywords that tell the web browser how to format the content
               </ul>
               
               HTML Elements:
               <ul>
                    <li> Usually consist of an opening tag, a closing tag, and some content 
                           between them <br>
                           <br>
                    <li> General format: &lt;TagName&gt; Contents &lt;/TagName&gt;
                         <ul> <br>
                              <li> &lt;TagName&gt; = opening tag
                              <li> &lt;/TagName&gt; = closing tag
                         </ul> 
                         <br>
                    <li> Attributes: Additional values accepted by some elements in their 
                           opening tags <br>
                         <ul> <br>
                              <li> Provide additional information to the browser
                              <li> General Format:  &lt;TagName AttributeName = 
                                                              "AttributeValue"&gt;
                                                              Contents &lt;/TagName&gt;
                         </ul>
                         <br>
               </ul>
               
          <br>
          <h2> HTML Tags </h2>
               <ul>
                    <li> Bold Tag: &lt;b&gt; Contents &lt;/b&gt; <br>
                    <br>
                    <li> Em Tag: &lt;em&gt; Contents &lt;/em&gt; <br>
                    <br>
                    <li> Anchor Tag: &lt;a href="url"&gt; LinkDisplay &lt;/a&gt;
                         <ul> <br>
                              <li> Creates a hyperlink to the url & names it LinkDisplay
                              <li> Example of a tag that uses an attribute (href)
                         </ul> 
                    <br>
                    <li> Image Tag: &lt;img src="url" alt="text"&gt; 
                         <ul> <br>
                              <li> Displays the image hosted at the src attribute value "url" 
                                     inline with text
                              <li> "url" = path to image, can be a local file on computer
                              <li> "text" = required attribute, displayed for a broken request 
                         </ul>
                    <br>
                    <li> Break Tag: &lt;br&gt;
                         <ul> <br>
                              <li> Creates a line break
                              <li> Inline element
                              <li> Void tag
                         </ul>
                    <br>
                    <li> Void Tag = tag with only an opening tag and no end tag because 
                         it does not have any content <br>
                    <br>
                    <li> Paragraph Tag: &lt;p&gt; Content &lt;/p&gt;
                         <ul> <br>
                              <li> Defines a paragraph
                              <li> Is a block element
                         </ul>
                    <br>
                    <li> Containers: use to add styles to text
                         <ul> <br>
                              <li> &lt;span&gt; Text &lt;/span&gt; = Creates an inline container element
                              <li> &lt;div&gt; Text &lt;/div&gt; = Creates a block container element
                         </ul>
                    <br>
                    <li> Inline and Block: <br>
                              <ul> <br>
                                   <li> Inline = element continues on current line
                                   <li> Block = element starts a new line and makes an invisible 
                                                      box with adjustable height and width
                              </ul>
               </ul>


          <br>
          <h2> Complete HTML Document Structure </h2>
          <b>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</b> 
          <ul> 
               <em> 
                    <li> Must be the very first thing in HTML document
                    <li> Defines the type of the document so the browser will render it correctly
               </em>
          </ul>
          
          <b>&lt;html&gt;</b>
          <ul>
               <em>
                    <li> Opening HTML tag
                    <li> Everything that shows on the webpage is placed within this tag
               </em>
          </ul>

          <blockquote>
               <b>&lt;head&gt;</b>
               <ul>
                    <em>
                         <li> Opening header tag, defines metadata for webpage
                         <li> Indented to a new level because the &lt;html&gt; tag 
                                was opened but not closed
                    </em>
               </ul>
          
                    <blockquote>
                    <b>&lt;title&gt; Title &lt;/title&gt;</b>
                         <ul>
                              <em>
                                   <li> Document title
                                   <li> Indented another level further because the &lt;head&gt; 
                                          tag was opened but not closed
                              </em>
                         </ul>
                    </blockquote>
                    
              <b>&lt;/head&gt;</b> <em> Closing header tag </em>
              </blockquote>

             <blockquote>
             <b> &lt;body&gt; </b> 
                    <ul>
                         <em> 
                              <li> Opening body tag
                              <li> Actual contents of document 
                         </em>
                    </ul>
               <b> &lt;/body&gt;</b> <em> Closing body tag </em>
               </blockquote>

          <b> &lt;/html&gt; </b> <em> Closing HTML tag </em>


          <br>
